                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d667">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.156/61: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1" type="to"
                            >Johnson</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-11-23T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 23, 1932—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>380. Your 1270, November 22, 4 p.m. As the Department has not been informed of
                    any changes in the situation upon which its instruction No. 699, February 19,
                    1932, was based, you should, unless you perceive and submit reasons to the
                    contrary, take the action directed in that instruction.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
